cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with storage area networks and proposes network coding schemes to improve quality of service metrics. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a likely category as the paper deals with distributed storage systems and proposes schemes to improve performance. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) is another likely category as the paper uses coding techniques to improve storage system performance. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper deals with managing multiple user types and proposes schemes to reduce saturation probability. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category as the paper deals with video storage and proposes schemes to improve performance.
